declarations.comments: Transforms a permutation into a product of disjoint cycles
declarations.title: abelize

declarations.comments:
Returns the number of permutations of whole elements
satisfying the provided type given by an array of cycle lengths.
For instance cardinality [2,2] 5 = cardinality [2,2,1] 5 = 15
for all permutations of type (ab)(cd)(e).
declarations.title: cardinality

declarations.comments:
Computes the reciprocal of the second polynomial
with the help of the previously computed 
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Resultant between
that polynomial and the minimal polynomial 
of the extension
declarations.title: cayley

declarations.comments: Where do elements land after a cycle
declarations.title: cycle

declarations.comments:
`cyclotomic n` returns the (irreductible) 
univariate minimal polynomial of degree `totient n`
whose roots are all the `totient n` primitive roots of unity
declarations.title: cyclotomic

declarations.comments: Where does an element land after a cycle
declarations.title: destination

declarations.comments: Discriminant of a univariate polynomial
declarations.title: discriminant

declarations.comments:
Builds the minimal polynomial whose root(s)
is (are) the sum of the roots of each of
the polynomials listed in the array
declarations.title: extensionBySum

declarations.comments:
Computes the required quantities needed to 
perform computations with algebraic extensions 
in the field of rational numbers
declarations.title: framework

declarations.comments:
Returns the set of elements generated by an set of permutations. 
Assumes set of products of disjoint cycles.
declarations.title: generate

declarations.comments:
Construit la liste des listes obtenues successivement 
par insertion de l'lment fourni aprs chacun des lments de la liste fournie 
et ce tant que l'lment en question n'est pas rencontr 
(fonction auxiliaire de permutationsR) :
declarations.title: insycleR

declarations.comments: Tests if the set of given elements is closed under group operation
declarations.title: isGroup

declarations.comments: Tests if the set of elements of given types is closed under group operation
declarations.title: isGroupType

declarations.comments: Partitions d'un ensemble en sous-ensembles :
declarations.title: makeBells

declarations.comments: Circular permutation of a cycle
declarations.title: nextRepresentation

declarations.comments:
Returns 1 if p = id, or k>1 s.t. p^(k-1) /= id and p^k = id  
Assumes product disjoint cycles
declarations.title: order

declarations.comments: Safe (defaulted) index
declarations.title: peek

declarations.comments:
Etablit la liste complte des permutations distinctes d'une liste 
mme en cas d'lments redondants :
declarations.title: permutationsR

declarations.comments: Where do elements land after a permutation
declarations.title: permute

declarations.comments: Deduces the disjoint cycles between a base and one of its permutations
declarations.title: play

declarations.comments:
Returns the type of a permutation, i.e. the list of orders 
of one of its expected representation as a product of disjoint cycles.
This type is notably the characteritic shared by every conjuate of the permutation,
in other words, the set of permutations sharing the same type
declarations.title: ptype

declarations.comments:
Computes the reciprocal of the first polynomial
in the extension whose minimal polynomial 
is provided by the second polynomial
declarations.title: reciprocal

declarations.comments:
Returns the number of permutations 
compound of products of exactly k disjoint cycles
over n elements.
For instance, stirling1 5 3 = 35 for
* 20 for cardinality of type (abc)(d)(e) and
* 15 for cardinality of type (ab)(cd)(e)
declarations.title: stirling1

declarations.comments:
Builds the https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sylvester_matrix
of two univariate polynomials with coefficients in a commutative ring
declarations.title: sylvester

declarations.comments: Euler Totient Function
declarations.title: totient
